-- Egypt bourse closed on July 1, shorter trading hours during Ramadan
-- 
-- Wed Jun 25, 2014 06:09AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, June 25 (Reuters) - Egypt's stock exchange <.EGX30> will stay closed for a bank holiday on July 1 and will operate with shortened trading hours during the Islamic fasting month of Ramadan as usual, the bourse said in a statement on Wednesday.

